<font color="#FF0000">RESPONSE TO JJ THE BOONIRAT</font><br>
<tt>Sun Feb  9  0:53:26 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
JJ<br>
The point is that many of us want the good night rest that you speak of.  That is why the hell I am on this site at all.<br><br>
A GAME? I don't think so, my friend.  This is as serious shit as it gets.  I want to heal.  Others want to heal.  Talking out the crap and garbage, hashing and re-hashing the shit that you, I and all the others went through is part of the process. A part of healing is learning, trying to be open to others views as they see/saw them through these many years, getting an understanding as to what and why things happened.  At this time, I am trying to deal with the anger and hostility, the bitterness and resentment and the fucken pain of the crap I went through after I returned home.  And you want to call this A GAME?.  There are people on this site, on this page that have answers for me, and YOU want me to back off?  No Fucken Way!!!<br><br>
There is validity in what you say about the uncaring, the unrespectful generation.  There is validity in what you say about the differences in experiences depending on the time you were in Nam.  What you fail to see is that the pain the person endured in '65 is the same pain the guy in '73 endured.  Different experience, same-same pain.  It all Fucken hurts.  <br><br>
You say you never met a protestor who gave a shit.  Neither have I!  I have never MET A PROTESTOR AT ALL!  That is why I am on this site.  <br><br>
Let me clue you in on something.  I have gotten more from these people on this site than from any time I spent at the local Vet Center listening to &quot;war stories&quot;.  Lord knows, I got a fist full of them, but I WANT TO FUCKEN EASE THE PAIN. I want to understand.  People like Arther, Mike, Nurse Ratchet, the Wrinklers, Tanker and a shitload of others have given me more than the six months I spent in the Menlo Park Veterans Program.  And I hope to get something from Sarah and anyone else who wants to contribute to this site.<br><br>
A INTELLECTUAL GAME?  If I was an intellectual, don't you think I would have this all figured out.  Get a life, champ, because you're fucking with mine!  You don't like it here, leave.  You want to contribute, stay.  Don't even think of telling us to &quot;ease up&quot;!
<p><code>-- docdel@maui.net  (Doc Del) </code><p>


